The paper deals with wireless communication systems and optimization of energy beamforming, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of multiple antennas at the hybrid access point (H-AP) and the analysis of achievable outage probability and average throughput suggest a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of closed-form expressions for suboptimal designs, which could fall under Multimedia (cs.MM) or Computer Communications (cs.COM).
